When compared to similar items, This product consumes less energy in farming and land-use, but more on packaging. A whopping 50% of lamb in the US is imported, so some of its carbon footprint comes from shipping. Eating a kilo of lamb is equivalent to driving about 90 miles.

When compared to similar items, This product consumes much less energy in farming and land-use, less energy for processing and less energy for transportation. Most of the greenhouse gases associated with this product come from feed production.
